    <main>
        <h2>The Four Pillars of Boston Sports</h2>
        <p class="intro">
            Boston is home to four legendary franchises — each representing a legacy of excellence, grit, and passion that defines the city’s identity.
        </p>

        <section class="team">
            <img src="First_Project/redsox-logo.webp" alt="Boston Red Sox logo">
            <div>
                <h3>Boston Red Sox</h3>
                <p>
                    Founded in 1901, the Red Sox are one of Major League Baseball’s most storied teams. 
                    From breaking the “Curse of the Bambino” in 2004 to their nine World Series titles, the Sox have been the heart of New England baseball.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>9× World Series Champions (most recent: 2018)</li>
                    <li>Home Stadium: Fenway Park</li>
                    <li>Iconic Players: Ted Williams, David Ortiz, Carl Yastrzemski</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="team">
            <img src="First_Project/celtics-logo.webp" alt="Boston Celtics logo">
            <div>
                <h3>Boston Celtics</h3>
                <p>
                    The Celtics have defined NBA greatness for decades, with 18 championships and a history of legendary players who shaped the game itself.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>18× NBA Champions (most recent: 2024)</li>
                    <li>Home Arena: TD Garden</li>
                    <li>Iconic Players: Bill Russell, Larry Bird, Paul Pierce</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="team">
            <img src="First_Project/patriots-logo.webp" alt="New England Patriots logo">
            <div>
                <h3>New England Patriots</h3>
                <p>
                    Once underdogs, the Patriots became the NFL’s modern dynasty. 
                    With six Super Bowl titles, their dominance under Bill Belichick and Tom Brady marked one of the greatest runs in sports history.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>6× Super Bowl Champions (most recent: 2018)</li>
                    <li>Home Stadium: Gillette Stadium (Foxborough, MA)</li>
                    <li>Iconic Players: Tom Brady, Rob Gronkowski, Tedy Bruschi</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="team">
            <img src="First_Project/bruins-logo.webp" alt="Boston Bruins logo">
            <div>
                <h3>Boston Bruins</h3>
                <p>
                    The Bruins are one of the NHL’s Original Six teams, with a history of toughness and skill. Their black and gold colors symbolize Boston’s hardworking spirit on the ice.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>6× Stanley Cup Champions (most recent: 2011)</li>
                    <li>Home Arena: TD Garden</li>
                    <li>Iconic Players: Bobby Orr, Ray Bourque, Patrice Bergeron</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
